claim.claim-text:
An electric appliance monitor method, adapted to monitor an aging condition and an abnormal state of an electric appliance (10) coupled to an electric supply, and comprising:
setting a load boundary of the electric appliance (10), (S410), wherein the load boundary is related to a reflection coefficient of the electric appliance (10) in a normal state;
detecting the electric appliance (10) to obtain a measured power factor, a measured root-mean-square voltage and a measured power related to the electric appliance (10) and simultaneously recognizing a supply frequency of the electric supply (S420);
calculating a real part of a load current and an imaginary part of the load current based on the measured power factor, the measured root-mean-square voltage, the measured power and the supply frequency (S430), wherein the real part of the load current and the imaginary part of the load current are related to a reflection coefficient of the electric appliance (10) during a current usage state;
displaying the load boundary and a coordinate point (Cp) representing to the real part of the load current and the imaginary part of the load current on a real-imaginary current coordinate system (S440); and
determining whether to execute a protection process corresponding to the electric appliance (10) according to the load boundary, the real part of the load current and the imaginary part of the load current (S450).
